<div class="accordion-wrapper">
<!-- Scheduling an Inspection -->
<div class="accordion" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
<span>Scheduling an Inspection</span>
<span class="accordion-arrow">▶</span>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<ul>
    <li>To schedule an inspection, residents can request an inspection in View Point Cloud by <a href="https://stamfordct.portal.opengov.com/" target="_blank">Clicking Here</a>.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li>Simply, navigate to your account, select the record you'd like to request an inspection for and select the "Inspection" step on the left-hand side of the page. Please include contact info on all inspection requests.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
    <li style="margin-left: 40px;"><strong>Please note:</strong> You will not be able to schedule an inspection until you’ve received all departmental approvals, the fee has been paid and the permit has been issued.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Canceling an Inspection -->
<div class="accordion" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
<span>Canceling an Inspection</span>
<span class="accordion-arrow">▶</span>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<ul>
    <li>To cancel an inspection, please <a href="https://stamfordct.seamlessdocs.com/f/PRCR" target="_blank">complete this form</a>.</li>
</ul>
</div>
<!-- Inspection Procedures -->
<div class="accordion" onclick="this.classList.toggle('active')">
<span>Inspection Procedures</span>
<span class="accordion-arrow">▶</span>
</div>
<div class="panel">
<ul class="inspection-procedures">
    <li>After a building permit has been issued, if applicable, HVAC, Plumbing and Electrical permits must be obtained before work is performed.</li>
    <li>After rough work has been done in walls and ceilings, rough inspections must be called in for plumbing, HVAC and electrical work.</li>
    <li>After all rough inspections have been completed and signed off, a framing inspection needs to be called in before closing walls and ceilings.</li>
    <li>After the framing inspection has been successfully conducted and work has been completed, final inspections must be called in and approvals obtained from all relevant departments.</li>
    <li>Upload all required closeout documents, and request a plan review appointment to have the Certificate of Occupancy issued.</li>
    <li>When Plumbing, HVAC, Electrical, Fire Protection, Roof and Siding permit has been issued without a building permit, a final inspection must be called in and approvals obtained before a Certificate of Approval can be issued.</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
